6 An Act relating to state procurement; creating the
Procurement Protection Act of 2025; providing short
7 title; defining terms; prohibiting certain entities
from entering into contracts with certain companies;
8 requiring certain disclosure statements; providing
penalties; providing exceptions to certain
9 prohibitions; providing for noncodification;
providing for codification; and declaring an
10 emergency.
11
12
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
15 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
16 This act shall be known and may be cited as the “Procurement
17 Protection Act of 2025”.
